==English==

===Etymology===
Transliteration of Hebrew יהוה Causative form ([[Hiphil]]) of the verb "havah" (הוה) "to be / to become". "He causes to be" or "He comes to be".  The word deliberately uses the vowel sounds from "adonai" (אדני) "lord".

